<%- include('../partials/html-head') %>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/break-habits/index.css">
<%- include('../partials/nav') %>

<main>
  <div class="dropdown-container">
    <div class="dropdown">
      <button class="dropdown-btn">?</button>
      <div class="dropdown-content">
        <h1>
          The Habit Loop
        </h1>
        <p>Habits are easy to change once you know about the habit loop.</p>
        <div class="habit-loop">
          <img src="/images/HabitLoop.png" alt="habitloop">
          <div class="habit-loop-info">
            <ul>
              <p>Every habit has a cue, routine, and reward </p> 
              <li>Cue: the signal that initializes your routine </li>
              <li>Routine: the habit itself</li>
              <li>Reward: the feedback we get from performing the habit</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p>To then "break" a habit, we must just change the routine</p>
        <p>Sounds easy enough, however often we don't know what the cue is, or we believe the reward to be something that it's not.</p>
        <p>That's where this habit log comes in. You will be taking steps to figure out what the cue and reward for your habit are. Once you know that, you will be one step closer to breaking that habit!</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <h1><%= title %></h1>
  <div class="bad-habit-container">
    <% habits.forEach(habit => { %>
      <a href="/break-habits/<%= habit._id %>">
        <div class="bad-habit-content">
      <%= habit.routine %> 
      </a>
    </div>
    <% }) %>
  </div>
  <a href="/break-habits/new">
    <button class="stop-btn">Stop a bad habit</button>
  </a>
</main>

<%- include('../partials/footer') %>